cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel feature learning framework for salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also utilizes deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new loss function, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
